case.name: She's Babbling
case.description: Y'shtola must strip off her bra, so she's trying to calm herself down by talking to herself. It does not appear to be working.

case.name: Glamoured Necklace
case.description: After taking off her necklace, Y'shtola will let the table know its appearance is due to a glamour spell and it's not actually valuable.

case.name: Rule Check
case.description: If someone at the table has an "Innocent" tag, Y'shtola will ask if everyone is clear on the rules and stakes of the game.

case.name: Fellow Mage
case.description: Y'shtola sees there is someone with the "magical" tag at the table and asks them what kind of practitioner they are.

case.name: Calamity
case.description: Y'shtola notices someone is armed at the table. She asks if there is something they're worried about.

notes.note: It's well established in FFXIV that healing magic cannot mend grevious wounds or regrow limbs. Just want to make it clear that this is not a lead in to Y'shtola trying to fix Dunban's injury, but seeing as she doesn't know the extent/nature of the damage she would naturally offer to heal him since it's well within her ability to fix more mundane injuries.
